latestPosts.caption:
LA is home to so many beautiful souls from all walks of life - and I genuinely love how this city makes space for everyone💗 As an immigrant myself, I’ve been lucky to meet people here who’ve changed my life forever. My mom is an immigrant. Many of my friends are too. And I wouldn’t be where I am today - working as a creator and living my dream - if it weren’t for the privilege of having legal status.

But the truth is, many aren’t so lucky. They work just as hard (if not harder), contribute so much to this country, and still live in fear or uncertainty.

So this is a reminder that LA is for everyone. No matter your background, your story, or your status - you belong. Always🫶
